  "domain": {
    "code": "HCM",
    "name": "Human Capital Management",
    "description": "Core HR system of record covering worker data, organization and position management, self-service, and lifecycle workflows. The HRIS / system-of-record layer of the HR stack.",
    "parent_domain_code": null,
    "certification_required": false,
    "catalog_tagline": "Run the single source of truth for your workforce, from the employee record to org structure, positions, and the full hire-to-retire lifecycle.",
    "catalog_description": "Human Capital Management is the system of record for your people. Maintain every worker's core profile, employment contracts, and the org structure they sit in, then drive each change through a governed workflow: hiring, transfers, promotions, leaves of absence, and offboarding. Self-service lets employees and managers raise and track their own changes while HR retains approval control.\n\nBecause the worker record is authoritative, the lifecycle events you record here ripple cleanly downstream: a new hire provisions access and payroll, a termination recalls assets and closes accounts, a promotion updates compensation. You define jobs and positions once, plan headcount against them, and keep compliance evidence in step with the regulations that apply to your workforce."
  },
